description._content: Metro-Cammell DMUs meeting at Princes Street Gardens, just outside Edinburgh Waverley station, in June 1963. At this time, many DMUs had the 'speed whiskers' seen here, before these were overpainted with yellow warning panels.. These DMUs - later 'Class 101' - were first introduced in 1956, and some were still in service in 2003.. Today, these tracks are electrified.. Original slide - photographer unknown See where this picture was taken.

The Edinburgh castle is awe inspiring. No wonderful they choose to build it on that hill since it makes the castle dominate the city and the surrounding country side. Try attacking up that slope straight ahead.....ain't going to work. 

I also liked the lush green trees in Scotland; they give the castle a nice setting. Including the fence also helps give the picture perspective and combines nicely with the castle in the background.

Looking down on Princes street in Edinburgh. This is the main street in Edinburgh and offers great shopping, bustling life and spectacular views of the castle on the left. I really wish I had a zoom back then....
